<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 (1) kohaldamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications for application of &sect; 18 (1) of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kuni 2002. aasta 1. juulini v&otilde;ib spetsialisti tunnistust taotleda ja spetsialistina t&ouml;&ouml;tada ka isik, kes ei ole omandanud k&otilde;rgharidust, kuid kes on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt viimase 18 kuu jooksul v&auml;&auml;rtpaberituru kutselises osalises v&otilde;i fondivalitsejas ja on alustanud k&otilde;rghariduse omandamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Until 1 July 2002, persons who have not acquired higher education but have worked in a professional securities market participant or a management company for at least the last eighteen months and have commenced the acquisition of higher education may also apply for a specialist's certificate and work as specialists. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kehtivad tunnistused, mis on v&auml;lja antud enne 1997. aasta 1. oktoobrit, kaotavad kehtivuse nende kehtimist&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;i nende k&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaselt kehtetuks tunnistamisel, kuid mitte hiljem kui viie aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel nende v&auml;ljaandmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Valid certificates which have been issued before 1 October 1997 become invalid upon expiry of the term thereof or revocation thereof according to this Act, but not later than within five years after the issue thereof. </inglise>
